ila-udem/blocks/issues/877"}, {"body": "True, but as long as we have persistent ids for parameters it is still kind of great, I think :)\r\n\r\nI thought a bit more about your latest proposal, and I have questions, so we should probably talk at the lab.", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/mila-udem/blocks/issues/comments/151165802", "created_at": "2015-10-26T15:00:29Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/mila-udem/blocks/pull/877#issuecomment-151165802", "updated_at": "2015-10-26T15:00:29Z", "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rizar/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rizar/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rizar/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/rizar", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rizar/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/rizar", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rizar/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/654434?v=3", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rizar/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rizar/received_events", "gravatar_id": "", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rizar/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "site_admin": false, "login": "rizar", "type": "User", "id": 654434, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rizar/followers"}, "id": 151165802, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/mila-udem/blocks/issues/877"}, {"body": "@rizar all right! I'll wait for you then!", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/mila-udem/blocks/issues/comments/151166472", "created_at": "2015-10-26T15:02:57Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/mila-udem/blocks/pull/877#issuecomment-151166472", "updated_at": "2015-10-26T15:02:57Z", "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Thrandis/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Thrandis/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Thrandis/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/Thrandis", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Thrandis/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/Thrandis", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Thrandis/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/10479248?v=3", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Thrandis/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Thrandis/received_events", "gravatar_id": "", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Thrandis/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "site_admin": false, "login": "Thrandis", "type": "User", "id": 10479248, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Thrandis/followers"}, "id": 151166472, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/mila-udem/blocks/issues/877"}, {"body": "@rizar here is the new serialization where you have a `dump` and a `load` function that are similar to the ones from `pickle`. The main difference is that the parameters can be dumped separately.\r\nThen there is the function `add_to_dump` that allows you to add more objects to the existing archive. The nice feature is that if the parameters are the same as the ones already in the archive, then you can pass them to the parameter `parameters` and they are not serialized a second time!", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/mila-udem/blocks/issues/comments/151970072", "created_at": "2015-10-28T19:49:40Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/mila-udem/blocks/pull/877#issuecomment-151970072", "updated_at": "2015-10-28T19:49:40Z", "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Thrandis/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Thrandis/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Thrandis/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/Thrandis", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Thrandis/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/Thrandis", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Thrandis/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://a